{"id": "duc04-testb-18:6#18", "contents": "House Speaker-elect Robert L. Livingston shocked his Republican colleagues on Thursday night by admitting to past adulterous affairs. Livingston revealed that he had been made aware of individuals working with the media to investigate his personal background and potentially exploit any indiscretions against him and his party on the eve of the impeachment vote. In a statement, Livingston acknowledged that he had \"on occasion strayed from my marriage\" during his 33-year marriage to his wife, Bonnie, and that these indiscretions had nearly cost him his marriage and family."}
